signature.instructions:
Extract structured bibliographic data from a scanned Swiss library catalog card image.

If you receive a `card_image`, focus on extracting the bibliographic data and formatting it into the JSON schema. Pay close attention to the rules for determining the 'type' field (Dissertation or thesis vs. Reference) based on the presence of 's.' on a separate line. Ensure that all required fields are populated, using 'null' for missing optional fields. Prioritize extracting the title, author's last and first names, publication year, place, pages, publisher, and format. Also, extract the shelfmark and subjects for the library reference. Always output a valid JSON object following the specified schema.

If you encounter special characters or unusual symbols in the title, ensure they are correctly encoded or transliterated to maintain the accuracy of the extracted title. Prioritize extracting the title accurately, even if it requires additional processing to handle encoding issues.

fields.description:
A JSON object with the extracted bibliographic data from the library card image.
The JSON must follow this exact schema:
{
  "type": {"type": "Dissertation or thesis" OR "Reference"},
  "author": {"last_name": "string", "first_name": "string"},
  "publication": {
    "title": "string",
    "year": "string",
    "place": "string or null",
    "pages": "string or null",
    "publisher": "string or null",
    "format": "string or null",
    "editor": "string or null"
  },
  "library_reference": {
    "shelfmark": "string or null",
    "subjects": "string or null"
  }
}

Rules:
- If the card contains "s." on a separate line, type is "Reference"; otherwise "Dissertation or thesis".
- Use null for missing optional fields.
- Remove " S." suffix from pages values.
- Format is usually "8", "8'" or "4".
- Shelfmark often begins with "Diss." or "AT".
